Ordination and clustering

metric scaling a.k.a. principal coordinates analysis (PCoA) that maps observed dissimilarities linearly onto low-dimensional graph using the same dissimilarities we had in our clustering.

ord <- cmdscale(dist_spp)
ordiplot(ord)
Species scores not available
ordihull(ord, cl, lty=3)
ordispider(ord, cl, col="blue", label=TRUE)
ordiellipse(ord, cl, col="red")
the matrix is either rank-deficient or indefinite

Manipulating dendrogram

den <- as.dendrogram(caver)

In the following we rearrange the dendrogram so that the ordering of leaves corresponds as closely as possible with the first ordination axis:

x <- scores(ord, display = "sites", choices = 1)
oden <- reorder(den, x)
#We plot the dendrorgrams together:
par(mfrow=c(2,1))
plot(den)
plot(oden)
par(mfrow=c(1,1))

The vegemite function has a graphical sister function tabasco2 that can also display the dendrogram. Moreover, it defaults to rerrange the dendrogram by the first axis of Correspondence Analysis:

species[which(rowSums(species)<=0),]
